        <param name="propertyName">The CLR name of the property to find.</param>
        <param name="validationOptions">The <see cref="T:Microsoft.Extensions.Validation.ValidationOptions" /> used to resolve metadata for super-types.</param>
        <summary>
            Finds the <see cref="T:Microsoft.Extensions.Validation.ValidatablePropertyInfo" /> for a member with the specified
            <paramref name="propertyName" />, including members inherited from base types or implemented
            interfaces.
            </summary>
        <returns>The matching <see cref="T:Microsoft.Extensions.Validation.ValidatablePropertyInfo" />, or <see langword="null" /> if no
            member with the specified name is declared on <see cref="P:Microsoft.Extensions.Validation.ValidatableTypeInfo.Type" /> or any of its super-types.</returns>
        <remarks>
          <para>
            Members declared directly on <see cref="P:Microsoft.Extensions.Validation.ValidatableTypeInfo.Type" /> take precedence over members inherited
            from super-types, matching the order in which <see cref="M:Microsoft.Extensions.Validation.ValidatableTypeInfo.ValidateAsync(System.Object,Microsoft.Extensions.Validation.ValidateContext,System.Threading.CancellationToken)" />
            visits members.
            </para>
          <para>
            Inherited members are resolved by looking up each super-type via
            <paramref name="validationOptions" />'s <see cref="P:Microsoft.Extensions.Validation.ValidationOptions.Resolvers" />. Super-types that
            are not registered with a resolver are silently skipped.
            </para>
        </remarks>
      </Docs>
